\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Approximate Inverse Square Law for 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 rays
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Vivek Sagar, Prashansa Gupta and Atul Singh Arora
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this experiment, we investigate the dependence of intensity of gamma
 radiation on the distance of the source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Motivation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We would like to model the dependence of intensity of gamma radiation being
 received.
 For this purpose, we carry out the following experiment, note the values
 of intensity on distance at which the source is kept.
 It can be seen that this comes out to be an inverse square law dependence.
 Let us assume a general power-law dependence as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
r\propto d^{-\alpha}
\]

\end_inset

The slope from the plot of 
\begin_inset Formula $\log r$
\end_inset

 versus 
\begin_inset Formula $\log d$
\end_inset

 gives the power 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Procedure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Operate the GM counter at the previously determined operating voltage i.e.
 485V, and set the preset time to 60 seconds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Three sets of background counts were taken.
 Placed the source in the end window detector stand.
 Beginning with the first slot, recorded three sets of counts for the set
 voltage.
 Repeated the procedure, increasing the distance, until the last slot was
 reached.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A graph of distance versus the counts was plotted, and error bars determined.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Observations and Calculations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The graph of distance versus the counts shows the inverse square dependence
 of intensity on the distance.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another graph plots the log of both the counts and the distance, whose slope
 gives the square power.
 
\end_layout

